# .trivyignore
# Acknowledged Trivy findings that are accepted with documented justification
# Reviewed by: DevOps team
# Review cadence: Quarterly
# Last reviewed: March 2026

# cross-spawn CVE-2024-21538
# Justification: cross-spawn is a transitive dependency of Jest (devDependency).
# It is not present in production runtime — only installed during the test stage
# of the Docker build. The production image runs npm ci --omit=dev which excludes
# all devDependencies. Risk to production: None.
CVE-2024-21538

# glob CVE-2025-64756
# Justification: glob is a transitive dependency of Jest (devDependency).
# Same reasoning as cross-spawn above. Not present in production runtime.
CVE-2025-64756

# minimatch CVE-2026-26996, CVE-2026-27903, CVE-2026-27904
# Justification: minimatch is a transitive dependency of Jest (devDependency).
# Upgrading to the fixed major version breaks Jest's internal test-exclude module.
# Not present in production runtime. Risk to production: None.
CVE-2026-26996
CVE-2026-27903
CVE-2026-27904

# tar CVE-2026-23745, CVE-2026-23950, CVE-2026-24842, CVE-2026-26960,
#     CVE-2026-29786, CVE-2026-31802
# Justification: tar is used internally by npm for package installation.
# It is not called by application code at runtime. The production container
# does not run npm after startup — tar has no execution path in production.
# Risk to production: None.
CVE-2026-23745
CVE-2026-23950
CVE-2026-24842
CVE-2026-26960
CVE-2026-29786
CVE-2026-31802
